Name: Test1
Skill.Definition: Knowledge of the portfolio of 84.51 client capabilitiesE: Basic understanding of vision and customer value generated by each capability areaI: Continued depth of knowledge across capability areas, beginning to develop expertise of solutions within a capability area and an understanding of which solutions are appropriate to solve clients’ business needs.A: Full understanding of solutions and capability areas.

Name: Test1
Skill.Definition: Focus on self-improvement and the development of relevant skills and competencies.E:  Learn – Learning new things through project experiences, trainings, and available industry newsI: Learn / Do – Integrating acquired skills and knowledge into project workA: Learn / Do / Teach – Proven track record of applying learning and teaching others

Name: Test1
Skill.Definition: Ability to develop solutions to answer complex issues. E: Ability to identify problems and appropriate solutions related to assigned projectsI: Ability to scope and deliver practical solutions to answer client business questionsA: Ability to analyze complex data to solve challenging problems, including development of new complex methodologies and having a vision for scalable products and solutions.

Name: Test1
Skill.Definition: Development of new solutions or improvements to existing ideas based on industry trends and client needs. E:  Identifying opportunity areas to improve the efficiency of existing solutionsI:  Productionalizing the process for existing solutions, allowing it to be utilized by others.  Re-applying existing solutions in new ways.A: Development of new solutions, including methodology development, process development, and commercialization.

Name: Test1
Skill.Definition: Ability to move projects through the lifecycle: ideation, scoping, execution, and deliveryE:  Focus on efficient project execution and delivery.  I:  Project scoping to meet client needs.  Collaborating with relevant capability teams, driving best in class projects.  A:  Capability / sector workplan development.  Focus on commercial strategy.  Efficient project and team resourcing.

Name: Test1
Skill.Definition: Ability to execute a project with excellenceE:  Delivering work to a high standardI:  Driving delivery excellence through the effective utilization of your network; Ability to identify risks / potential issues.A:  Accountable for efficient execution of highly complex projects, identifying teams and skills that need to be involved.

Name: Test1
Skill.Definition: Collaboration with team membersE:  Behaving as an active participant of a project team, working with others to deliver shared goalsI:  Fostering collaborative teamwork for all projectsA:  Creating a collaborative working environment

Name: Test1
Skill.Definition: Having and communicating a vision; passionately working towards the vision;  bringing others with you along the wayE: Project LevelI:  Team Level + Leading by Example + DelegationA:  Organizational Level

Name: Test1
Skill.Definition: Short term project coaching and competency development.  Long term relationship building and career development.E:  Providing support to the broader analytical community.  I:  Acting as a trusted analytical advisor to team members and direct reports.  Identifying gaps in team, proactively developing appropriate L&D plans.  A: Recognizing strength and opportunity areas for each team member, helping to achieve career goals of the broader analytical community.

Name: Test1
Skill.Definition: Developing a strong internal and external professional networkE:  Building relationships with colleagues, inside and outside of your teamI: Building loyal relationships with colleagues and clientsA: Utilizing networks to build partnerships and expertly navigate across 84.51, Kroger, and CPGs.

Name: Test1
Skill.Definition: Exhibiting professional behavior in every situationE: Following company policies and procedures;  Communicating (written and verbal) in a clear and professional manner;  Showing respect for people around you;  Knowing when to flag issues, ask questions and seek out helpI: Exhibiting verbal and non-verbal responses in stressful situations;  Accepting responsibility for issues;  Managing client expectations and delivering on commitmentsA:  Managing difficult client / employee conversations;  Role-modelling 84.51 values everyday

Name: Test1
Skill.Definition: Understanding of when and how to use the many data assets 84.51° has access to  - Kroger Plus Card Data, Qualitative, Quantitative, Demographic, Rest of Market, etc. Recognize when and where new data assets are needed, and why.  E:   Basic understanding of the value and unique contribution of each type of data we have.  Knowledge of what data we do not have access to at 84.51I:   Experience working on projects where multiple data assets are leveraged.  Able to explain the value of our data assets to internal and external clients.  A:  Deep knowledge of how data assets align to business questions and ability to lead and coach others on how to best leverage them.

Name: Test1
Skill.Definition: Ability to work with internal and external clients on discovery, client engagement, project design, and data interpretation. Can identify what resources and teams are needed to execute a project.  Create feasible and actionable recommendations for client to implement.E: Basic understanding of client objectives and how projects lead to outcomes that meet these objectivesI: Full understanding of client objectives and ability to identify exisiting solutions or the need for new solutions to meet those objectivesA: Active participation in defining client business objectives and recommendations in accordance with long term strategic vision

Name: Test1
Skill.Definition: Can create an analytical plan including key milestones, expected output, and accurate timelines; Effective communication to project group of progress/issues; Keep a project moving from beginning to end.E: Follow a plan and adhere to timelines I: Develop plans and set timelines accordingly; Lead the analytical plan of Blueprint/Established projects from beginning to end with little oversightA: Lead all aspects (project team, stakeholders, etc) of any Blueprint/Established/Exploratory project from beginning to end; Escalates problems when appropriate

Name: Test1
Skill.Definition: Ability to manage expectations of project stakeholders, knowing when to make leadership aware of outcomes/solutions/hurdles.E: Understands the role of stakeholders within projectsI: Works closely with stakeholders to ensure clients objectives are met A: Able to identify the appropriate stakeholders of a project; Proactively works to keep stakeholders up to speed on project progress/outcomes/hurdles

Name: Test1
Skill.Definition: Can create holistic insights & conclusions considering data from multiple sources from across 84.51° assets & capabilities.  Can design and deliver actionable insights from data.  Has instincts to know when there are potential issues and knows how to recognize and solve them.  Can use gut-checks to sense check data and prevent QA issues at end of project.E: Ability to generate insights from data.  Can execute against the scope of a project and deliver error-free analyses.  asic understanding and exposure to the diversity of data available across 84.51° assets & capabilities.I: Can apply the derived insights into business recommendations.  Ability to adjust insights plan when data is not telling a compelling story.  Ability to make conclusions from multiple 84.51° data sources; ability to tell a story which brings together diverse types of data, and deal with conflicting data points from different sources.  Ability to create a deliverable that successfully weaves together multiple data types, working with the project team. A: Can connect the insights to overall business climate.  Ability to identify challenges to implementation of recommendations and can provide relevant solutions.  Can provide support and consult on others' projects with useful feedback and guidance.  Extensive history of examples of integrated projects; able to coach and mentor others on integrating data & insights.

Name: Test1
Skill.Definition: Ability to tell a story with data through effective visual and verbal communication.  Keeps the complex simple.E: Identifies the data points necessary to build the customer story; Leverages best practice visual data bank.  Can articulate why the data is meaningful.I: Develops effective stories with limited input from others; Contributing to the best practice visual data bank. Can respond effectively to ad hoc questions during presentations.A: Can develop strong stories from data, as well as leading others in this area.  Ability to lead conversation and take audience through the story

Name: Test1
Skill.Definition: Ability to create value for clients by understanding business context of projects and providing relevant solutions to their problems.  Has ability to estimate cost to determine if value is appropriate for the amount of effort/cost involved. E: Basic understanding of value creation of each project and how it supports/drives the overall workplanI: Understands the value derived from each project executed and recommends changes to scope to align value to costA: Build workplan that creates maximum value for clients;  Ability to prioritize projects and manage workplans to maximize value.
